ctSysType.name: ctSysType
ctSysType.description: System Type ie. VMC8250, Other etc.,

ctSysPrimaryBackupMode.name: ctSysPrimaryBackupMode
ctSysPrimaryBackupMode.description: Primary/Backup Mode of the Channel Extender. This is defined in PARAMTAB.DAT

ctSysAutoStartFlag.name: ctSysAutoStartFlag
ctSysAutoStartFlag.description: State of the auto start flag. Set to 1, enable or online to turn channel extender ONLINE or to 0 disable or offline to turn channel extender OFFLINE Note! Turning OFFLINE will automatically restart the the channel extender with a RESTARTEXEC request.

ctSysPowerSupplyMonitorFlag.name: ctSysPowerSupplyMonitorFlag
ctSysPowerSupplyMonitorFlag.description: Whether EXEC is monitoring the power supply or not

ctSysChannelExtenderMode.name: ctSysChannelExtenderMode
ctSysChannelExtenderMode.description: State of the EXEC i.e. whether it is in diagnostics mode or channel extender mode

ctSysElapsedTime.name: ctSysElapsedTime
ctSysElapsedTime.description: For how long the system has been running expressed in days, hours, minutes.

ctSysStartupTime.name: ctSysStartupTime
ctSysStartupTime.description: The last time EXEC was restarted expressed in Month, Day, Year, Hour, Minute format in the local time zone.

ctSysCurrentTime.name: ctSysCurrentTime
ctSysCurrentTime.description: Current Time expressed in Month,Day,Year,Hour,Minute format in the local time zone.

ctSysCustomerName.name: ctSysCustomerName
ctSysCustomerName.description: Textual Identification of the name of the customer

ctSysComputermContact.name: ctSysComputermContact
ctSysComputermContact.description: The textual identification of the contact person at Computerm, together with information on how to contact this person.

ctSysGMXCommand.name: ctSysGMXCommand
ctSysGMXCommand.description: Issue select GMX command via SNMP. Supported Commands: SWC, <channel_number_and_address>, <network_address>, <num_contiguous> channel_number_and_address-Hexadecimal-Mandotory network_address-Hexadecimal-Mandatory num_contiguous-Decimal-Optional

ctHwEntry.name: ctHwEntry
ctHwEntry.description: Information about each hardware module installed

ctHwSlotIndex.name: ctHwSlotIndex
ctHwSlotIndex.description: Slot Index of the hardware board. For system level modules, a specific slot number will be reserved. See the top of this document for details.

ctHwBoardIndex.name: ctHwBoardIndex
ctHwBoardIndex.description: The board index for a specific slot e.g. ARTIC card and AIB daughter cards. This can also be used to include the extenally connected modules e.g. OC3/DS3 converter, Control Unit etc.,

ctHwPortIndex.name: ctHwPortIndex
ctHwPortIndex.description: Port Number of the board. This can be potentially used for MUX cards and Peripheral devices.

ctHwDeviceIndex.name: ctHwDeviceIndex
ctHwDeviceIndex.description: Externally connected devices index. This can be potentially used for peripheral devices and OC3/DS3 converters

ctHwSpeed.name: ctHwSpeed
ctHwSpeed.description: Speed of the hardware module. This is the baud rate for comm. modules

ctHwChannelOrLineNumber.name: ctHwChannelOrLineNumber
ctHwChannelOrLineNumber.description: Channel Number of the Adapter/Emulator boards and Line Number of the Comm boards. For other board types, this value will be zero.

ctHwRevisionLevel.name: ctHwRevisionLevel
ctHwRevisionLevel.description: Revision level of the hardware module

ctSwEntry.name: ctSwEntry
ctSwEntry.description: Information about each software module running.

ctSwSlotIndex.name: ctSwSlotIndex
ctSwSlotIndex.description: Slot Index of the hardware module where this software module is running. For system level modules, a specific slot number will be reserved. See the top of this document for details.

ctSwBoardIndex.name: ctSwBoardIndex
ctSwBoardIndex.description: The board index for a specific slot e.g. ARTIC card and AIB daughter cards where this software module is running. This can also be used to include the extenally connected modules e.g. OC3/DS3 converter, Control Unit etc.,

ctSwPortIndex.name: ctSwPortIndex
ctSwPortIndex.description: Port Number of the board this software module is running. This can be potentially used for MUX cards

ctSwDeviceIndex.name: ctSwDeviceIndex
ctSwDeviceIndex.description: Externally connected devices index. This can be potentially used for peripheral devices and OC3/DS3 converters

ctTopologyTable.name: ctTopologyTable
ctTopologyTable.description: Provides the connectivity information between the current channel extender and all the remote units including their twin units.

ctTopoSlotIndex.name: ctTopoSlotIndex
ctTopoSlotIndex.description: Slot Index of the hardware module this connection is describing. To describe the current unit's twin unit, a specific slot number will be reserved. See the top of this document for details.

ctTopoBoardIndex.name: ctTopoBoardIndex
ctTopoBoardIndex.description: The board index of the slot this connection is describing.

ctTopoPortIndex.name: ctTopoPortIndex
ctTopoPortIndex.description: The port index of the slot this connection is describing.

ctTopoDeviceIndex.name: ctTopoDeviceIndex
ctTopoDeviceIndex.description: Externally connected devices index. This can be potentially used for peripheral devices and OC3/DS3 converters

ctTopoName.name: ctTopoName
ctTopoName.description: Textual description of this connection. Same as ctHwName.

ctTopoRemoteUnit.name: ctTopoRemoteUnit
ctTopoRemoteUnit.description: Address of the remote channel extender unit.

ctTopoRemoteTwinUnit.name: ctTopoRemoteTwinUnit
ctTopoRemoteTwinUnit.description: Address of the remote twin channel extender.

ctPerfResetAllCompressionRatios.name: ctPerfResetAllCompressionRatios
ctPerfResetAllCompressionRatios.description: This variable is used to reset the compression ratios for all different device types

ctPerfResetAllPeakThroughputs.name: ctPerfResetAllPeakThroughputs
ctPerfResetAllPeakThroughputs.description: Use this object to reset the peak throughput values (Tx, Rx and Total) associated with this conceptual row. This will start a new data collection and new peak values will be computed. Modifying this object will also reset the ctPerfPeakThroughputStartTime to the current system time

ctPerfResetAllReceiveErrorCounts.name: ctPerfResetAllReceiveErrorCounts
ctPerfResetAllReceiveErrorCounts.description: Use this object to reset the receive error values associated with all the comm. lines. This will start a new data collection. Modifying this object will also reset the ctPerfReceiveErrorCountStartTime to the current system time

ctPerfShowFractions.name: ctPerfShowFractions
ctPerfShowFractions.description: Use this object to display the CPU/Line Utilization and CompressionRatio in 1/100th of a percentage. Example: CompressionRatio: 1.59 Please note that 1.59 cannot be reported to the NMS since SNMP doesn't support Floating Point Arithmetic. The following are the alternatives:: ctPerfShowFractions=Off: Agent Reports 2 (1.59 rounded up) as the CompRatio to the NMS ctPerfShowFractions=On: Agent Reports 159 (1/100th of a percentage) as the CompRatio to the NMS. This will give better precision. If the NMS has the capability to devide by 100, using this method, the actual CompRatio of 1.59 can be displayed by the NMS. By Default, ctPerfShowFractions is OFF

ctPerfControlTable.name: ctPerfControlTable
ctPerfControlTable.description: Provides the user modifiable values for performance data

ctPerfControlEntry.name: ctPerfControlEntry
ctPerfControlEntry.description: Provides the objects to configure performance data collection

ctPerfControlDeviceIndex.name: ctPerfControlDeviceIndex
ctPerfControlDeviceIndex.description: Externally connected devices index. This can be potentially used for peripheral devices and OC3/DS3 converters

ctPerfControlInterval.name: ctPerfControlInterval
ctPerfControlInterval.description: Data collection interval specified in seconds

ctPerformanceTable.name: ctPerformanceTable
ctPerformanceTable.description: Performance data for the channel extender units

ctPerformanceEntry.name: ctPerformanceEntry
ctPerformanceEntry.description: Provides the performance data for different hardware modules of a Channel Extender

ctPerfBoardIndex.name: ctPerfBoardIndex
ctPerfBoardIndex.description: Board index for a specific slot

ctPerfDeviceIndex.name: ctPerfDeviceIndex
ctPerfDeviceIndex.description: Externally connected devices index. This can be potentially used for peripheral devices and OC3/DS3 converters

ctPerfTxThroughput.name: ctPerfTxThroughput
ctPerfTxThroughput.description: Transmit thorughput specified in bits/second (including any overhead bits). This value is defined for communication adapters only and calculated for each pyhsical line. If a physical line is using multiple virtual lines, this value accounts for all the virtual lines

ctPerfRxThroughput.name: ctPerfRxThroughput
ctPerfRxThroughput.description: Receive thorughput specified in bits/second (including any overhead bits). This value is defined for communication adapters only and calculated for each pyhsical line. If a physical line is using multiple virtual lines, this value accounts for all the virtual lines

ctPerfTotalThroughput.name: ctPerfTotalThroughput
ctPerfTotalThroughput.description: Total thorughput specified in uncompressed bytes/second. This value is defined for adapters, emulators, compression boards, and for each device assigned to a particular adapter or emulator

ctPerfPeakTxThroughput.name: ctPerfPeakTxThroughput
ctPerfPeakTxThroughput.description: Peak Transmit thorughput specified in bits/second (including any overhead bits). This value is defined for communication adapters only and calculated for each pyhsical line. If a physical line is using multiple virtual lines, this value accounts for all the virtual lines. ctPerfPeakThroughputStartTime and ctPerfPeakTxThrouthputTime identify start time of the data sampling and the actual the time when the peak value was noted. User can reset the current peak value and start new data collection by using the ctPerfResetPeakThroughput mib object

ctPerfPeakTxThroughputTime.name: ctPerfPeakTxThroughputTime
ctPerfPeakTxThroughputTime.description: Time stamp when the peak transmit throuput value was noted. Time is specified in the local time zone

ctPerfPeakRxThroughput.name: ctPerfPeakRxThroughput
ctPerfPeakRxThroughput.description: Peak receive thorughput specified in bits/second (including any overhead bits). This value is defined for communication adapters only and calculated for each pyhsical line. If a physical line is using multiple virtual lines, this value accounts for all the virtual lines. ctPerfPeakThroughputStartTime and ctPerfPeakRxThrouthputTime identify start time of the data sampling and the actual the time when the peak value was noted. User can reset the current peak value and start new data collection by using the ctPerfResetPeakThroughput mib object

ctPerfPeakRxThroughputTime.name: ctPerfPeakRxThroughputTime
ctPerfPeakRxThroughputTime.description: Time stamp when the peak receive throuput value was noted. Time is specified in the local time zone

ctPerfPeakTotalThroughput.name: ctPerfPeakTotalThroughput
ctPerfPeakTotalThroughput.description: Peak total thorughput specified in uncompressed bytes/second. This value is defined for adapters, emulators, compression board and for all the devices assigned to each adaptor or emulator. ctPerfPeakThroughputStartTime and ctPerfPeakTotalThrouthputTime identify start time of the data sampling and the actual the time when the peak value was noted. User can reset the current peak value and start new data collection by using the ctPerfResetPeakThroughput mib object

ctPerfPeakTotalThroughputTime.name: ctPerfPeakTotalThroughputTime
ctPerfPeakTotalThroughputTime.description: Time stamp when the peak total throughput value was noted. Time is specified in the local time zone.

ctPerfPeakThroughputStartTime.name: ctPerfPeakThroughputStartTime
ctPerfPeakThroughputStartTime.description: Time stamp when the data sampling was started for determining peak values. Time is specified in the local time zone. Whenever user resets the peak values by setting the ctPerfResetPeakThroughput, this object will be updated with the current system time

ctPerfResetPeakThroughput.name: ctPerfResetPeakThroughput
ctPerfResetPeakThroughput.description: Use this object to reset the peak throughput values (Tx, Rx and Total) associated with this conceptual row. This will start a new data collection and new peak values will be computed. Modifying this object will also reset the ctPerfPeakThroughputStartTime to the current system time

ctPerfTxUtilization.name: ctPerfTxUtilization
ctPerfTxUtilization.description: This value is defined only for the communication adapters and computed for each physical line. This value is expressed as the transmit bits/second as a percentage of the line data rate. This value can be between 0 and 100 inclusive

ctPerfRxUtilization.name: ctPerfRxUtilization
ctPerfRxUtilization.description: This value is defined only for the communication adapters and computed for each physical line. This value is expressed as the receive bits/second as a percentage of the line data rate. This value can be between 0 and 100 inclusive

ctPerfCPUUtilization.name: ctPerfCPUUtilization
ctPerfCPUUtilization.description: This value is defined only for adapters, emulators, compression board and mother board. This value represents the extent the CPU on the specified board is busy servicing all of the hardware and software components installed in the system. This value can be between 0 and 100 inclusive

ctPerfDataRate.name: ctPerfDataRate
ctPerfDataRate.description: The data rate associated with the communication line and is expressed in bits/second. For SDLC lines, although both Tx and Rx data rates are available, only Tx clock will be used to represent the data rate. For ATM and LAN cards, the data rate values specified in the PARAMTAB.DAT will be provided

ctPerfReceiveErrorCount.name: ctPerfReceiveErrorCount
ctPerfReceiveErrorCount.description: This value is defined only for communication adapters and shown as the number of errors received over the sampling interval(default =60 secs). Ideally this value will be calculated using a rolling 60 second window to allow errors to be displayed as they occur

ctPerfReceiveErrorCountStartTime.name: ctPerfReceiveErrorCountStartTime
ctPerfReceiveErrorCountStartTime.description: This is the system time when the last reset Receive Errors command was received

ctPerfResetReceiveErrorCount.name: ctPerfResetReceiveErrorCount
ctPerfResetReceiveErrorCount.description: This variable is used to reset the Receive Erors associated with this conceptual row. Resetting will start a new data collection. This will also set the ctPerfReceiveErrorCountStartTime to current time.

ctPerfCommLineDelay.name: ctPerfCommLineDelay
ctPerfCommLineDelay.description: Communication line delay expressed in milli seconds. Valid only for Comm. adapters

ctPerfCompressionRatio.name: ctPerfCompressionRatio
ctPerfCompressionRatio.description: Compression ratio is defined for the compression board, for each channel adapter, and emulator and for each device assigned to the adapter and emulator. This is a cumulative value calculated from the time when the customer sends a reset compression ratio using the ctPerfResetCompre -ssionRatio object.

ctPerfCompressionRatioStartTime.name: ctPerfCompressionRatioStartTime
ctPerfCompressionRatioStartTime.description: This is the system time when the last reset compression ration command was received

ctPerfResetCompressionRatio.name: ctPerfResetCompressionRatio
ctPerfResetCompressionRatio.description: This variable is used to reset the compression ratio associated with this conceptual row

ctPerfDeviceTxUncompressedCounts.name: ctPerfDeviceTxUncompressedCounts
ctPerfDeviceTxUncompressedCounts.description: This is the transmit uncompressed byte count for a device Note: When ctPerfShowFractions is OFF this value is expressed in kilobytes

ctPerfDeviceTxCompressedCounts.name: ctPerfDeviceTxCompressedCounts
ctPerfDeviceTxCompressedCounts.description: This is the transmit compressed byte count for a device Note: When ctPerfShowFractions is OFF this value is expressed in kilobytes

ctPerfDeviceRxUncompressedCounts.name: ctPerfDeviceRxUncompressedCounts
ctPerfDeviceRxUncompressedCounts.description: This is the receive uncompressed byte count for a device Note: When ctPerfShowFractions is OFF this value is expressed in kilobytes

ctPerfDeviceRxCompressedCounts.name: ctPerfDeviceRxCompressedCounts
ctPerfDeviceRxCompressedCounts.description: This is the receive compressed byte count for a device Note: When ctPerfShowFractions is OFF this value is expressed in kilobytes

ctPerfDeviceCountsStartTime.name: ctPerfDeviceCountsStartTime
ctPerfDeviceCountsStartTime.description: This is the system time when the last reset device counts command was received

ctPerfResetDeviceCounts.name: ctPerfResetDeviceCounts
ctPerfResetDeviceCounts.description: This variable is used to reset the transmit, receive, compressed and uncompressed counts for a device

ctPerfTxDeviceCompressionRatio.name: ctPerfTxDeviceCompressionRatio
ctPerfTxDeviceCompressionRatio.description: This is the transmit compression ratio for a device

ctPerfRxDeviceCompressionRatio.name: ctPerfRxDeviceCompressionRatio
ctPerfRxDeviceCompressionRatio.description: This is the receive compression ratio for a device

ctPerfResetAllDeviceCounts.name: ctPerfResetAllDeviceCounts
ctPerfResetAllDeviceCounts.description: This variable is used to reset the transmit, receive, compressed and uncompressed byte counts of all devices back to zero

ctDiagnosticsTable.name: ctDiagnosticsTable
ctDiagnosticsTable.description: Diagnostics information for the Channel Extenders

ctDiagnosticsEntry.name: ctDiagnosticsEntry
ctDiagnosticsEntry.description: Diagnostics information for each hardware module of the Channel Extender.

ctDiagSlotIndex.name: ctDiagSlotIndex
ctDiagSlotIndex.description: Slot index of the hardware module where the diagnostics test is being performed

ctDiagBoardIndex.name: ctDiagBoardIndex
ctDiagBoardIndex.description: Board index of the slot where the diagnostics test is being performed.

ctDiagPortIndex.name: ctDiagPortIndex
ctDiagPortIndex.description: Port index of the board where the diagnostics test is being performed.

ctPerfDeviceIndex2.name: ctPerfDeviceIndex2
ctPerfDeviceIndex2.description: Externally connected devices index. This can be potentially used for peripheral devices and OC3/DS3 converters

ctAbortEntry.name: ctAbortEntry
ctAbortEntry.description: Channel Extender Aborts History Table Entry

ctAbortIndex.name: ctAbortIndex
ctAbortIndex.description: This index uniquely identifies an entry in the Abort Table. Although the maximum number of entries in the table is limited to some pre-determined value (20 in phase I), ctAbortIndex can assume values in the 1..65535 range

ctAbortAlertTimeStamp.name: ctAbortAlertTimeStamp
ctAbortAlertTimeStamp.description: Trap occurence time expressed in local time zone

ctAbortAlertShortDescription.name: ctAbortAlertShortDescription
ctAbortAlertShortDescription.description: Short Description of the abort or alert being described

ctAbortAlertDescription.name: ctAbortAlertDescription
ctAbortAlertDescription.description: Full description of the abort or alert being described
